headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 22 points while playing with Kevin Durant and James Harden for the first time in three months, leading the Brooklyn Nets to a 105-91 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets finally get Big 3 back together, beat Bulls 105-91

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 28 points and LeBron James returned after a six-game absence to score 24 Saturday to lead the Los Angeles Lakers to a 122-115 victory over the Indiana Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: James returns as he and Davis send Lakers by Pacers 122-115

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 33 points, 13 assists and 10 rebounds, and led an overtime surge that sent the New York Knicks past the Charlotte Hornets 118-109 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle leads Knicks past Hornets in OT, tie Atlanta for 4th

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 26 points and 11 rebounds as the short-handed Boston Celtics cruised to a 124-108 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Celtics cruise to 124-108 win over Timberwolves

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 27 points and the Phoenix Suns maintained their hope of earning the top spot in the Western Conference with a 140-103 victory over the short-handed San Antonio Spurs on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns rout short-handed Spurs 140-103, keep hope for top seed

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton and Bryn Forbes each scored 21 points to help the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Miami Heat 122-108 on Saturday night in a potential first-round playoff series preview.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Heat 122-108, maintain bid for East's No. 2 seed
